 Here's a JavaScript function that uses regular expressions to extract the three character code from a filename in the format "57-1Jn.usfm":

```javascript
function extractCode(filename) {
    // Regular expression to match three character codes (upper or lower case letters or digits)
    var regex = /[a-zA-Z0-9]{3}/;

    // Split the filename by the dot and then by the hyphen, take the second part of the resulting array
    var parts = filename.split('.');
    var code = parts[0].split('-')[1];

    // Use regular expression to extract the three character code from the second part of the filename
    var match = regex.exec(code);

    // If there is a match, return it; otherwise, return null
    return match ? match[0] : null;
}
```

You can use this function like this:

```javascript
var filename = "57-1Jn.usfm";
var code = extractCode(filename); // Returns "1Jn"
```
